description:
This role offers an excellent opportunity to quickly build upon your accounting, tax and financial management experience. You will form part of a team providing accounting and advisory support to international businesses from a diverse range of industries.

Responsibilities:

Under the guidance of your Senior, develop your understanding of the: business model, drivers of financial performance and accounting and tax risks for each of the clients in your portfolio;
Ensure accurate recording of accounting transactions and analyse financial information, to prepare meaningful monthly management accounts and supporting schedules;
Prepare financial statements under SFRS and other international GAAP;
Prepare GST returns and assist with tax compliance matters;
Coordinate with external parties including external auditors, tax agents, corporate secretarial and government authorities, where required;
Work with other Mazars teams, domestic and international, to meet client’s needs;
Establish good client relationships through positive interactions with the client’s team and
Involve in any other adhoc duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Bachelor or Diploma in Accountancy, or related finance disciplines
Candidates with no experience are welcome to apply
Good knowledge of Microsoft Excel; knowledge of accounting software (XERO, SAP and/or NetSuite) is an advantage
Team player with good communication, interpersonal and client servicing skills
Meticulous, attention to detail and good organisational skills
Able to work under pressure and tight deadlines

