description:
Our laboratory is growing rapidly and we are currently seeking a full-time Laboratory Assistant to join our team. This position will work with a team to accomplish tasks and projects that are instrumental to the company’s success. If you want an exciting career where you can tap on your previous expertise and develop and grow your career further, this is the opportunity for you.
Responsibilities

Inspect specimen samples, verify accuracy and quantity according to study protocol/laboratory manual;
Accession specimens into inventory system and perform data entry;
Prepare and coordinate all biological laboratory sample shipments for storage and shipments;
Order and follow up with vendors on reagents, preventive maintenance contracts.
Daily routine tasks and other necessary support to the Laboratory Technicians and Lab Director.

Qualifications

Minimum Diploma in any field;
At least 2 years of industry experience in related similar position;
Team-worker and detail-oriented with good time management skills;
Basic knowledge of Microsoft® Word and Excel;
8:30am to 5:30pm to be worked over 5 days between Monday to Saturday (Saturdays being rotational). Able to work on public holidays.

